> >    1. Follow the instructions detailed here for getting yourself an apple
> >    developer program cert :
> >    http://code.google.com/p/selenium/wiki/SafariDriver#Getting_Started
> >    2. Make sure that you have added your cert into Safari browser.
> >    3. Now download the extension from here :
> >    http://code.google.com/p/selenium/downloads/detail?name=SafariDriver....
> >    4. Unzip this file to a directory.
> >    5. Finally, install the extension by following steps (6 - 11).
> >    6. Launch Safari.
> >    7. Make Developer menu visible (if its not already) by clicking on the
> >    wheel icon (on the top right corner of your screen), and choosing
> >    Preferences > Advanced > "Show Develop menu in menu bar"
> >    8. Now click on the menu icon (a page like icon right next to the
> >    wheel icon)
> >    9. Open the Extension Builder (Develop > Show Extension Builder)
> >    10. Add a new extension: (By referring to the directory where you
> >    unzipped the downloaded zip file)
> >    11. Click Install
> >    12. For Grid runs make sure you have configured your Grid and nodes as
> >    detailed in this thread  :
> >    http://groups.google.com/group/webdriver/browse_thread/thread/f1ebe93...